entry.title: test #2
entry.summary: The post from wtogami at apache.org is not subscribed to the list and should be auto-rejected by the server. If the message goes through, it indicates a configuration problem. The email includes an HTML attachment that has been scrubbed, so no information can be gleaned from it. It's important to ensure that only subscribed email addresses can send messages to prevent unauthorized individuals or spam from clogging up the list. Overall, the post serves as a reminder to double-check list configurations to maintain list efficiency and security.
